Cell["\<\
Both the \"BFGS\" and \"Newton\" methods require to evaluate gradients of the \
QSP, which is harder than evaluation of the QSP itself. In this respect, the \
\"FixedPointIterations\" method, which does not require the gradients, is \
better (the convergence in terms of the number of iterations seems to be \
slower, though).\
\>", "Notes",
 CellID->865893351,ExpressionUUID->"651c6fa1-3522-440f-abc0-a10bf46ec7f4"]
}, Dynamic[CurrentValue[
 EvaluationNotebook[], {TaggingRules, "Openers", "NotesSection"}, Closed]]]],

