    "history" -> {"14.0", "14.3", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {
     "quantum signal processing", "quantum singular value transform", 
      "quantum eigenvalue transform"}, "specialkeywords" -> {}, 
    "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True, "label" -> 
    "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> "QuantumMob/Q3",
     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "QSPFind[{a1, a2, ..., an} -> p] returns the quantum signal processing \
(QSP) that represents the desired polynomial with reduced list {a1, a2, ..., \
an} of Chebyshev expansion coefficients and parity p (\\[PlusMinus]1 for even \
and odd parity, respectively). QSPFind[{c0, c1, c2, ..., cn}] assumes {c0, \
c1, c2, ..., cn} to be a full list of Chebyshev expansion coefficients of a \
polynomial of degree n, and automatically converts it to a reduced list \
according to the parity implied in the full list. If the parity is indefinite \
or indeterminate, then $Failed is returned with a warning message.", 
    "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "QSPFind", 
    "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> 
    "QSPFind", "type" -> "Symbol", "uri" -> "QuantumMob/Q3/ref/QSPFind"}},
